cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SE

The paper deals with security protocols and their defense in networked systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the network topology and the use of guardians to defend the protocols, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of graphs to model the network topology, which is related to the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of inference to detect ongoing attacks, which is related to the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the approach to defend flawed security protocols, which is related to the category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
